 Real-Time Web Monitoring Dashboard

 Context

 Current training only outputs JSONL log files and console prints. This plan adds a real-time web monitoring dashboard so users can observe training metrics live, monitor multiple
  experiments simultaneously, and trigger emergency stops from a browser UI.

 New File Structure

 monitor/
     __init__.py
     app.py              # FastAPI app: REST + WebSocket + static serving
     callback.py         # MonitorCallback for Trainer integration
     static/
         index.html      # Vue 3 SPA (CDN, no build step)
 tests/
     test_monitor.py     # WebSocket, disconnect, stop command tests

 Modified files: train.py, cli.py, requirements.txt

 Phase 1: FastAPI Backend (monitor/app.py)

 Data model:
 @dataclass
 class ExperimentState:
     experiment_id: str
     hyperparams: dict
     metrics: deque[dict]       # maxlen=1000
     stop_requested: bool
     status: str                # "running" | "stopped"

 In-memory dict experiments_cache: dict[str, ExperimentState] keyed by experiment_id.

 Endpoints:

