 WebSocket manager: ConnectionManager maintains dict[str, set[WebSocket]]. On metric POST, broadcast to all subscribers for that experiment. Wrap send() in try/except; remove dead
  connections on failure.

 Key decisions:
 - Stop signal returned in the metrics POST response body ({"stop": true/false}) — avoids a second network call per episode
 - Bounded deque (1000) prevents memory growth
 - Hyperparams set on first metric arrival (included in first POST payload)

 Phase 2: Callback + Trainer Integration

 monitor/callback.py — MonitorCallback class:
 - __init__(monitor_url, experiment_id, hyperparams) — creates httpx.Client(timeout=2.0)
 - on_episode_end(episode, total_reward, policy_loss, value_loss, entropy, episode_length, lr, gamma, lam) -> bool — POSTs metrics, returns stop flag
 - ALL exceptions caught silently (training never interrupted)
 - close() — closes httpx client

 train.py changes (minimal):
 1. Trainer.__init__ adds monitor_callback=None parameter, stores it
 2. In Trainer.train(), after structured_logger.log_episode(...) (line ~474), add:
   - Call monitor_callback.on_episode_end(...) if set
   - If returns True: save model, close logger, return {"stopped": True, ...}
 3. At end of train() before return: call monitor_callback.close() if set

 Phase 3: CLI Changes (cli.py)

 1. Add --monitor-url / -m option to train command
 2. If provided, import and instantiate MonitorCallback before creating Trainer
 3. Pass monitor_callback to Trainer()
 4. After trainer.train() returns, check result.get("stopped") → set DB status to "stopped"
 5. Add new monitor command that runs uvicorn monitor.app:app

 Phase 4: Vue 3 Frontend (monitor/static/index.html)

 Single HTML file, CDN dependencies (Vue 3, Chart.js). No npm build.

 Features:
 - Experiment dropdown (refreshed every 5s via /api/experiments)
 - WebSocket connection per selected experiment
 - Real-time reward curve (line chart)
 - Real-time loss curves (policy_loss + value_loss)
 - Hyperparameters table
 - Latest metrics display
 - Connection status indicator (green/red dot)
 - Emergency Stop button → POST /api/experiments/{id}/stop

 Disconnect handling:
 - ws.onclose → show red indicator, start 3-second reconnect timer
 - On reconnect, fetch full history via REST to catch up

 Multi-experiment: Switching dropdown closes old WS, opens new one, fetches history via REST. No interference between experiments.

 Phase 5: Tests (tests/test_monitor.py)

 Using pytest + httpx.AsyncClient with ASGITransport:

 1. Message format: POST metric → connect WS → verify JSON schema arrives
 2. Disconnect handling: Connect WS → close → POST metrics → verify no server crash → reconnect → fetch history via REST
 3. Stop command delivery: POST stop → POST metric → verify response {"stop": true}
 4. Callback failure isolation: MonitorCallback with unreachable URL → on_episode_end() returns False, no exception raised
 5. Multi-experiment isolation: Register metrics for 2 experiments → verify no cross-contamination

 Phase 6: Dependencies

